    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.00716.003_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">London<ptr target="loc.00716_n1"/></name>
                    <date when="1881-12-06" rend="right">Dec 6<hi rend="underline"><hi
                                rend="superscript">th</hi></hi>&#8212;81</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>To my Dear Friend M<hi rend="underline"><hi rend="superscript">r</hi></hi>
                    Whitman,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I sit now in my hall on duty, to write you these few lines, to let you know that I am
                Well. Only hoping that this letter will find you enjoying good <choice>
                    <orig>Health</orig><reg>health</reg></choice>. I received all your Papers, <choice><sic>Whitch</sic><corr>which</corr></choice> you sent me, and also seen your New
                Book, <choice><sic>Whitch</sic><corr>which</corr></choice> Is for sale in our city, I have <choice><sic>ben</sic><corr>been</corr></choice>
                some what surprised on
                not receiving A
                letter from you, but I suspect I must excuse you for not writing, on account of you Being so <choice>
                    <sic>buisy</sic>
                    <corr>busy</corr>
                </choice> this <choice><sic>sumer</sic><corr>summer</corr></choice>, but I hope you will not Delay in answering this
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.00716.004_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                    
                <choice>
                    <orig>Has</orig>
                    <reg>as</reg>
                </choice> I should like to have a letter from you, For I like to read your letters
                very <choice>
                    <orig>mutch</orig><reg>much</reg></choice>, <choice>
                    <orig>Wee</orig>
                    <reg>We</reg>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <orig>ar</orig>
                    <reg>are</reg>
                </choice> having some <choice>
                    <orig>nise</orig>
                    <reg>nice</reg>
                </choice> weather now, <choice>
                    <orig>Wee</orig>
                    <reg>We</reg>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>aint</sic>
                    <corr>ain't</corr>
                </choice>
                <choice>
                    <sic>hade</sic>
                    <corr>had</corr>
                </choice> no cold Weather this fall, yet. Things in the asylum is quite lively now
                the Dances and Plays is in full blast now, And they make the Winter pass away quite
                lively, Dr. Bucke and family And all the asylum People is Well I am now night watch in the Refractory under Dr <unclear reason="illegible"
                    resp="#ss" cert="medium"><choice><orig>Beamer</orig><reg>Beemer</reg></choice></unclear>
                <choice>
                    <orig>whoo</orig>
                    <reg>who</reg>
                </choice> is a warm friend of yours, and often times <choice><sic>askes</sic><corr>asks</corr></choice> me, When I heard from
                you.</p>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc.00716.005_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <p>Dr. Bucke was telling me that you was come over to visit him this winter <choice><orig>Cum</orig><reg>Come</reg></choice> right along we will <choice>
                    <orig>Bee</orig>
                    <reg>Be</reg>
                </choice> all glad to see you come, <choice>
                    <orig>Every body</orig>
                    <reg>Everybody</reg>
                </choice>
                <hi rend="underline">loves you</hi>, and you <choice><sic>wount</sic><corr>won't</corr></choice> be no Stranger this time and you will like It <choice>
                    <orig>hear</orig>
                    <reg>here</reg>
                </choice> in the Winter. I <choice>
                    <orig>gus</orig>
                    <reg>guess</reg>
                </choice> I will bring my letter to a close, By sending the Love of all the asylum <choice>
                    <orig>Employies</orig>
                    <reg>Employees</reg>
                </choice> to you, your name is never <unclear reason="illegible" resp="#nnk"
                    cert="medium"><choice><sic>ded</sic><corr>dead</corr></choice></unclear> With them,</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>I Remain</salute>
                <salute>Truly</salute>
                <salute>To you for Ever</salute>
                <signed rend="right">Tommy Nicholson<ptr target="loc.00716_n2"/></signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc.00716.006_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
